msgid "Compass"
msgstr "나침반"

msgid "Points to the world origin"
msgstr "월드 원점을 가리킴"

msgid "Compasses are tools which point to the world origin (X=0, Z=0) or the spawn point in the Overworld."
msgstr ""

msgid "A Compass always points to the world spawn point when the player is in the overworld.  In other dimensions, it spins randomly."
msgstr ""
"오버월드에 있을 때는 항상 월드의 스폰 지점을 가리킵니다. 다른 차원에서는 "
"무작위로 회전합니다."

msgid "Lodestone Compass"
msgstr ""

msgid "Points to a lodestone"
msgstr ""

msgid "Lodestone compasses resemble regular compasses, but they point to a specific lodestone."
msgstr ""

msgid "A Lodestone compass can be made from an ordinary compass by using it on a lodestone.  After becoming a lodestone compass, it always points to its linked lodestone, provided that they are in the same dimension.  If not in the same dimension, the lodestone compass spins randomly, similarly to a regular compass when outside the overworld.  A lodestone compass can be relinked with another lodestone."
msgstr ""

msgid "Recovery Compass"
msgstr ""

msgid "Points to your last death location"
msgstr ""

msgid "Recovery Compasses are compasses that point to your last death location"
msgstr ""

msgid "Recovery Compasses always point to the location of your last death, in case you haven't died yet, it will just randomly spin around"
msgstr ""

